						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#143;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#191;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#173; (HATAIRO) (&amp;#230;&amp;#151;&amp;#151;&amp;#229;&amp;#189;&amp;#169;) is a flag collecting game from Japan.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Let's draw the national flag. How many paints do I need to paint the flags of the world?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With five colors of red, blue, green, yellow and black, it is possible to draw 70% or more of the flags of the world. And if you add orange, sky blue and brown, you can paint almost all flags of the world.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Hatairo is a game that brings together the necessary colors, completes many national flags, and makes more valuable collections. The value of the national flag differs depending on the kind of color and the number of colors, and adding the national flag along the theme will add value to the work.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Make good use of paints and complete the watercolor paintings of flags around the world!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All you have to do is (A) Preparation for production, (B) Only one piece of work completed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(A) In preparation for production, select one flag card to be produced, and use the production cube to collect the necessary colors. &amp;#10;(B) In work completion, complete the national flag, place it in the gallery, and get a production cube or theme token.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when a player completes 9 flags or a total of 5 themes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is the player with the most points. Players get points from the victory points on flags, bonus points for themes, and a game end bonus (difference in the number of completed cards). Unfinished and discarded cards lose points.&amp;#10;publisher's summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
